---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Private Pilot Requirements: FAA PPL Checklist | Flight School Friend"
  description="A beginner-friendly checklist of private pilot requirements, including age, English, student pilot certificate, medical, flight hours, written test, solo, and checkride."
>
  <div class="bg-white pb-24">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">

      <div class="text-sm text-slate-500 mb-8 font-medium">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-sky-600 transition">Home</a> &rarr;
        <a href="/guides/" class="hover:text-sky-600 transition">Guides</a> &rarr;
        <span class="text-slate-900">Private Pilot Requirements</span>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-12">
        <span class="inline-block bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 text-xs font-bold px-3 py-1 rounded-full mb-4">Requirements</span>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-slate-900 mb-6 tracking-tight">Private Pilot Requirements: What You Need Before, During, and After Training</h1>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-slate-500 font-medium mb-8">
          <span>Reading time: 10 mins</span><span>&bull;</span><span>Updated: June 2026</span>
        </div>
        <a href="/flight-school-decision-tool/quiz/" class="inline-block px-6 py-3 bg-sky-600 text-white font-bold rounded-lg hover:bg-sky-500 transition">Take the Flight School Decision Tool</a>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-sky-500 p-6 rounded-r-2xl mb-12 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-lg mb-2">The Short Answer</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-700 font-medium">Private pilot requirements include eligibility (age/English), training, aeronautical knowledge, flight experience, solo preparation, a knowledge test, and a practical test. Always verify current FAA requirements with official sources and your instructor.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-12 relative items-start">
        <div class="lg:w-2/3 guide-content">
          <h2 id="checklist">Private pilot requirements checklist</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Age:</strong> Be at least 16 years old to fly solo, and 17 to get the actual certificate.</li>
            <li><strong>Language:</strong> Be able to read, speak, write, and understand English.</li>
            <li><strong>Medical:</strong> Hold at least a Third-Class FAA Medical Certificate (or BasicMed).</li>
            <li><strong>Student Cert:</strong> Obtain a Student Pilot Certificate via IACRA.</li>
            <li><strong>Knowledge:</strong> Pass the FAA Private Pilot Airmen Knowledge Test (written exam).</li>
            <li><strong>Flight Experience:</strong> Meet the minimum flight hour requirements for your chosen training path (Part 61 vs 141).</li>
            <li><strong>Checkride:</strong> Pass the Practical Test with a DPE.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 id="flight-experience">Flight training and aeronautical experience</h2>
          <p>The FAA establishes strict minimums. For the standard path:</p>
          <div class="bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-6 rounded-xl mb-6 shadow-sm text-slate-700 font-medium">
            Part 61 airplane single-engine requires at least 40 hours total, including at least 20 hours flight training from an authorized instructor and 10 hours solo flight training.
          </div>

          <h2 id="solo-requirements">Solo and cross-country requirements</h2>
          <p>Before you are allowed to fly the airplane by yourself, your instructor must endorse your logbook. The 10 hours of solo flight training must include at least 5 hours of solo cross-country flying, and one solo cross-country flight of at least 150 nautical miles total distance.</p>

          <div class="my-12 bg-sky-50 border border-sky-100 rounded-2xl p-8 text-center">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Want the private pilot starter checklist?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600 mb-6">Track your milestones from day one to checkride.</p>
            <form id="mid-email-form" class="max-w-md mx-auto flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-2">
              <input type="email" placeholder="Your email address" required class="flex-grow px-4 py-3 rounded-lg text-slate-900 outline-none border border-slate-200 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-sky-500" />
              <button type="submit" class="px-6 py-3 bg-sky-600 hover:bg-sky-500 text-white font-bold rounded-lg transition">Email me the PPL checklist</button>
            </form>
            <p id="mid-email-success" class="hidden text-green-600 font-medium mt-4">Got it — this checklist would be sent in the live version.</p>
          </div>

          <h2 id="medical-note">Medical certificate / BasicMed planning note</h2>
          <p>If you have a history of ADHD, depression, sleep apnea, or heart conditions, the medical certificate can become a massive hurdle. It is highly recommended to secure your medical certificate <em>before</em> you invest thousands of dollars into flight lessons.</p>

          <h2 id="prepare">What to prepare before starting</h2>
          <p>Create an IACRA account, schedule your FAA medical exam with an AME (Aviation Medical Examiner), and consider completing your ground school online before you start paying high hourly rates in the cockpit.</p>

          <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-slate-200 text-sm text-slate-500">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2 text-base">Sources & Verification</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-1 mb-4">
              <li><a href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-14/chapter-I/subchapter-D/part-61/subpart-E" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-sky-600 hover:underline">eCFR Part 61 Subpart E</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-14/chapter-I/subchapter-D/part-61/subpart-C/section-61.87" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-sky-600 hover:underline">eCFR 14 CFR 61.87 (Solo Requirements)</a></li>
            </ul>
            <p>This guide is for educational planning only. Always confirm current FAA requirements with your CFI, school, AME, DPE, or the FAA.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="lg:w-1/3 w-full">
          <div class="sticky top-24 bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 shadow-sm">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4 uppercase tracking-wider text-sm border-b border-slate-200 pb-2">In this guide</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-slate-600 font-medium">
              <li><a href="#checklist" class="hover:text-sky-600 transition">Private pilot requirements checklist</a></li>
              <li><a href="#flight-experience" class="hover:text-sky-600 transition">Flight training experience</a></li>
              <li><a href="#solo-requirements" class="hover:text-sky-600 transition">Solo requirements</a></li>
              <li><a href="#medical-note" class="hover:text-sky-600 transition">Medical certificate note</a></li>
              <li><a href="#prepare" class="hover:text-sky-600 transition">What to prepare before starting</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-16 pt-12 border-t border-slate-200">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">Related Guides</h2>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
          <a href="/guides/flight-school-cost/" class="block bg-white border border-slate-200 hover:border-sky-300 rounded-xl p-6 transition shadow-sm"><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Flight School Cost Guide</h3><p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Understand realistic private pilot training costs.</p></a>
          <a href="/guides/part-61-vs-part-141/" class="block bg-white border border-slate-200 hover:border-sky-300 rounded-xl p-6 transition shadow-sm"><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Part 61 vs Part 141</h3><p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Compare flexible and structured training paths.</p></a>
          <a href="/guides/how-to-choose-a-flight-school/" class="block bg-white border border-slate-200 hover:border-sky-300 rounded-xl p-6 transition shadow-sm"><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">How to Choose a Flight School</h3><p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Use a practical checklist to compare schools.</p></a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-slate-900 text-white rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-16 text-center mt-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Want a personalized starting path?</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-400 mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto text-lg">Take the Flight School Decision Tool to get a recommended roadmap based on your situation.</p>
        <a href="/flight-school-decision-tool/quiz/" class="inline-block px-8 py-4 bg-sky-600 hover:bg-sky-500 font-bold rounded-xl text-lg transition shadow-md">Start Here</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  document.getElementById('mid-email-form')?.addEventListener('submit', (e) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    (e.target as HTMLElement).classList.add('hidden');
    document.getElementById('mid-email-success')?.classList.remove('hidden');
  });
</script>
